Package: cufunctions
Title: Clinical Utility Functions for Statistical Analysis and Visualization
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Steve", "Holleran", email = "info@biomath.net", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Janak", "Ramakrishnan", role = "aut"))
Description: A collection of functions for common biostatistical analyses
    including ANOVA (one-way, two-way), ANCOVA, repeated measures, logistic
    regression, Cox proportional hazards, Kaplan-Meier curves, ROC analysis,
    scatter plots, and summary tables. Provides publication-ready plots via
    ggplot2 and comprehensive console output with post-hoc tests, significance
    letters, and model selection via dredge.
